Blade shape, length and airfoils are likely to be very specific for the application… taking into account motor torque, blade speed, whether you’re trying for high flow or high pressure. Noise. Look at how many different designs of computer fan you can find.

Agree with above, if you’re buying blades, could be you can get CAD from the source.

If you plan to print them, i think you’re going to be better off designing your own blade
